{"title_page": "Faro Airport", "text_new": "{{For|the airport in Yukon, Canada|Faro Airport (Yukon)}}\n{{Distinguish|Paro Airport}}\n{{Use dmy dates|date=March 2020}}\n{{Short description|International airport serving Faro, Portugal}}\n{{Infobox airport\n| nativename = <small>''Aeroporto Internacional de Faro''</small>\n| image2-width = 250\n| location = <!--If different than above-->\n|focus_city    =\n| elevation-m = 7\n| elevation-f = 24\n| metric-elev = Y\n| coordinates = {{coord|37|00|52|N|007|57|57|W|region:PT|display=inline,title}}\n| pushpin_label = LPFR\n| r1-surface = [[Asphalt]]\n| metric-rwy = Y\n| name = Faro Airport\n| image = <!--airport logo-->\n| image-width = 200\n| image2 = FAO FARO AIRPORT PORTUGAL FROM FLIGHT CDG-RAK EASYJET G-EFZI A319 (14778925195).jpg\n| IATA = FAO\n| ICAO = LPFR\n| type = Public\n| owner = ANA Aeroportos de Portugal, S.A.\n| operator = {{nowrap|[[ANA Aeroportos de Portugal]]}}\n| city-served = [[Faro, Portugal|Faro]], [[Algarve]], [[Portugal]]\n| pushpin_map = Portugal\n| pushpin_map_caption = Location within Portugal\n| website = [http://www.ana.pt/en-US/Aeroportos/algarve/Faro/Pages/HomeFaro.aspx ana.pt]\n| r1-number = 10/28\n| r1-length-m = 2,490\n| stat-year = 2018\n| stat1-header = Passengers\n| stat1-data = 8,685,571\n| stat2-header = Passengers change 17-18\n| stat2-data = {{decrease}} 0.5%\n| stat3-header = Aircraft Movements\n| stat3-data = 57,352\n| stat4-header = Movements change 17-18\n| stat4-data = {{decrease}} 0.2%\n| stat5-header = Cargo (t)\n| stat5-data = 120\n| stat6-header = Cargo change 17-18\n| stat6-data = {{increase}} 2.9%\n| footnotes = Sources: [[National Institute of Civil Aviation of Portugal|ANAC]],<ref>{{cite web | url = http://www.anac.pt/vPT/Generico/PublicacoesINAC/BoletinsEstatisticosTrimestrais/Paginas/BoletinsEstatisticosTrimestrais.aspx | title = Boletins Estat\u00edsticos Trimestrais | language = Portuguese | trans-title = Quarterly Statistical Bulletins | work = ANAC | publisher = Portuguese Civil Aviation Authority}}</ref> ANA,<ref>{{citation | url = https://www.ana.pt/en/system/files/documents/annual_report_2018.pdf| language = English | title = Annual Report 2018 | date = 15 May 2019 | location = Lisbon | publisher = [[ANA Aeroportos de Portugal]]}}</ref><ref>{{cite press release | url = http://www.ana.pt/pt-PT/Topo/Institucional/SobreANA/Imprensa/Noticias/Paginas/Maior-crescimento-de-sempre.aspx?fromlist=1 | url-status = dead | archive-url = https://web.archive.org/web/20160215163528/http://www.ana.pt/pt-PT/Topo/Institucional/SobreANA/Imprensa/Noticias/Paginas/Maior-crescimento-de-sempre.aspx?fromlist=1 | archive-date = 15 February 2016 | lang = Portuguese | title = Aeroportos portugueses com o maior crescimento de sempre | trans-title = Portuguese airports with the highest growth ever | date = 7 January 2016 | publisher = [[ANA Aeroportos de Portugal]]}}</ref> WAD<ref>{{cite web | url = https://worldaerodata.com/wad.cgi?id=PO93204 | title = FARO | work = World Aero Data | publisher = WorldAeroData.com | access-date = 2 March 2020}}</ref>\n}}\n\n'''Faro Airport''' (Portuguese: ''Aeroporto Internacional de Faro'') {{Airport codes|FAO|LPFR}}, also known as [[Algarve]] Airport, is located {{convert|4|km|abbr=on}} to the west<ref name=\"AIP\">AIP [http://www.nav.pt/ais/cd/2012_03_08_AIRAC/html/index.html Part 3 \u2013 AD 2 Aerodromes] {{Webarchive|url=https://web.archive.org/web/20120415051720/http://www.nav.pt/ais/cd/2012_03_08_AIRAC/html/index.html |date=15 April 2012 }}</ref> of [[Faro, Portugal|Faro]] in Portugal. The airport opened in July 1965.<ref>{{cite web |url=http://www.ana.pt/SiteCollectionDocuments/Negocios_Empresas/Sobre_Aeroportos/ALGARVE_PLANO_DIRECTOR.pdf |title=Archived copy |access-date=2014-07-29 |url-status=dead |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20140729183505/http://www.ana.pt/SiteCollectionDocuments/Negocios_Empresas/Sobre_Aeroportos/ALGARVE_PLANO_DIRECTOR.pdf |archive-date=29 July 2014}}</ref> A total of 6.4 million passengers used Faro airport in 2015. The airport became a hub for the first time in March 2010, when Ryanair decided to base seven of its aircraft there.<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.ryanair.com/ie/news/39th-base-faro-6ac-28-routes-and-1-3m-pax|title=Official Ryanair website - Cheap flights from Ireland - Ryanair}}</ref> It is very busy from March to October, to the extent that it becomes a slot coordinated airport.<ref name=\"Info\">{{cite web|url=http://www.therouteshop.com/faro-airport/#factsTab|title=Faro Airport (FAO) - Unserved Routes in the Route Shop}}</ref>\n\n==Facilities==\n[[File:2017-08-20 Arrivals hall at Faro airport.JPG|thumb|Inside the arrivals hall at Faro airport]]\n[[File:Vorplatz Flughafen Faro.jpg|thumb|The forecourt of the arrivals hall]]\n[[File:Aeroporto de Faro1.jpg|thumb|Terminal building]]\n[[File:Faro Airport at sunset 3.jpg|thumb|Terminal building]]\nFaro Airport is capable of handling six million passengers a year. There are 22 stands of which 16 are remote, with 60 check-in desks and 36 boarding gates.<ref name=\"Info\"/>\n\nSince its opening in 1966 Faro airport has had two major developments: the new passenger terminal building in 1989, and its enlargement in 2001. Faced with growing traffic demand and passenger safety and satisfaction needs, the development plan for 2009\u20132013 saw Faro airport undergo extensive improvements to runway and infrastructure, as well as a widespread renovation of the airport terminal and commercial areas.<ref>{{Cite web|url=https://www.airport-technology.com/projects/faro-international-airport-terminal-expansion/|title=Faro International Airport Terminal Expansion|website=Airport Technology|language=en-GB|access-date=2019-05-30}}</ref>\n\nAlong with the airports in Lisbon, Porto, Ponta Delgada, Santa Maria, Horta, Flores, Madeira, and Porto Santo, the airport's concessions to provide support to civil aviation were conceded to [[ANA Aeroportos de Portugal]] on 18 December 1998, under provisions of decree 404/98. With this concession, ANA became responsible for the planning, development and construction of future infrastructure.<ref>{{cite web|url=https://www.porto-airport-car-rental.com/the-history-of-porto-airport-francisco-de-sa-carneiro-airport/|title=The history of Porto Airport - Francisco de S\u00e1 Carneiro Airport|date=1 February 2017|website=Porto-Airport-Car-Rental.com|access-date=5 January 2018}}</ref>\n\n==Airlines and destinations==\nThe following airlines operate regular scheduled direct passenger flights at Faro Airport:\n\n{{Airport destination list\n<!-- -->\n| [[Aer Lingus]] | [[Dublin Airport|Dublin]]<br/>'''Seasonal:''' [[Cork Airport|Cork]], [[Shannon Airport|Shannon]]\n<!-- -->\n| [[Air France]] | [[Charles de Gaulle Airport|Paris\u2013Charles de Gaulle]] (begins 4 April 2020)<ref>{{cite web |last1=Liu |first1=Jim |title=Air France S20 Spain/Portugal network additions |url=https://www.routesonline.com/news/38/airlineroute/287074/air-france-s20-spainportugal-network-additions/ |website=Routesonline |accessdate=23 October 2019}}</ref>\n<!-- -->\n| [[Air Transat]] | '''Seasonal:''' [[Toronto Pearson International Airport|Toronto\u2013Pearson]]\n<!-- -->\n| [[British Airways]] | [[Gatwick Airport|London\u2013Gatwick]]<br/>'''Seasonal:''' [[London City Airport|London\u2013City]], [[Heathrow Airport|London\u2013Heathrow]], [[London Stansted Airport|London\u2013Stansted]]\n<!-- -->\n| [[Brussels Airlines]] | '''Seasonal:''' [[Brussels Airport|Brussels]]\n<!-- -->\n| [[Chair Airlines]] | '''Seasonal:''' [[Z\u00fcrich Airport|Z\u00fcrich]]\n<!-- -->\n| [[Corendon Airlines]] | [[Brussels Airport|Brussels]]\n<!-- -->\n| [[Corendon Dutch Airlines]] | '''Seasonal:''' [[Amsterdam Airport Schiphol|Amsterdam]], [[Maastricht-Aachen Airport|Maastricht/Aachen]]\n<!-- -->\n| [[easyJet]] | [[Belfast International Airport|Belfast\u2013International]], [[Berlin Sch\u00f6nefeld Airport|Berlin\u2013Sch\u00f6nefeld]], [[Bordeaux\u2013M\u00e9rignac Airport|Bordeaux