old II. The caption reads: ''A [[Constitutional monarchy|constitutional]] king''.\nFile:Caroline Lacroit, mistress of Leopold II of Belgium.png|Caroline LaCroix, Leopold's mistress.\nFile:Leopold ii belgien.jpg|Last photo of Leopold II before his death.\nFile:Leopold II Marie Henriette.JPG|Tomb of Leopold II and Marie Henriette.\nFile:MutilatedChildrenFromCongo.jpg|Mutilated people from Congo Free State\nFile:Victim of Congo atrocities, Congo, ca. 1890-1910 (IMP-CSCNWW33-OS10-19).jpg|Victim of the atrocities with a missionary, c.&nbsp;1890\u20131910\nFile:+0000001 Image Kr\u00f6nungsmedaille Leopold II - 17 Dezember 1865 - von L\u00e9opold Wiener, n\u00e9 le 2 juillet 1823 \u00e0 Venlo, mort le 11 f\u00e9vrier 1891 \u00e0 Bruxelles.jpg|Coronation Medal Leopold II \u2013 accession to the throne on 17 December 1865 \u2013 by L\u00e9opold Wiener.\n</gallery>\n\n==See also==\n{{Portal|Monarchy|Belgium|History|Biography}}\n* [[Abir Congo Company]]\n* [[Atrocities in the Congo Free State]]\n* [[\u00c9mile Banning]]\n* [[Congo Free State propaganda war]]\n* [[Crown Council of Belgium]]\n* [[Kings of Belgium family tree]]\n\n==References==\n{{Reflist|30em}}\n\n==Bibliography==\n{{refbegin}}\n* [[Neal Ascherson|Ascherson, Neal]]: ''The King Incorporated'', [[Allen & Unwin]], 1963. {{ISBN|1-86207-290-6}} (''1999 Granta edition'').\n* [[Adam Hochschild|Hochschild, Adam]]: ''[[King Leopold's Ghost|King Leopold\u2019s Ghost: A Story of Greed, Terror, and Heroism in Colonial Africa]]'', [[Mariner Books]], 1998. {{ISBN|0-330-49233-0}}.\n*Petringa, Maria: ''Brazza, A Life for Africa'', 2006. {{ISBN|978-1-4259-1198-0}}\n* Wm. Roger Louis and Jean Stengers: ''E.D. Morel's History of the Congo Reform Movement'', Clarendon Press Oxford, 1968.\n* \u00d3 S\u00edoch\u00e1in, S\u00e9amas and Michael O\u2019Sullivan, eds: ''The Eyes of Another Race: Roger Casement's Congo Report and 1903 Diary''. University College Dublin Press, 2004. {{ISBN|1-900621-99-1}}.\n* \u00d3 S\u00edoch\u00e1in, S\